 Mental Asylum Records, the home label of tech trance Dj/producer, Indecent Noise, celebrates its 2nd Birthday this August with the release of the 2nd album in their "Tales From The Mental Asylum" compilation series. Similar to Chapter 1 last year, Chapter 2 is mixed by label boss Indecent Noise and showcases more than 20 of the best released and yet to be released tracks of the labels second year of existence. Listeners can expect tracks from label regulars such as Jase Thirlwall, Mark Sherry, John Askew, Matt Bowdidge, James Dymond and Robbie van Doe as well as new comers such as Acid Test, Paul Denton, Sam Jones & Rhys Thomas, Johan Ekman and Paul Denton amongst others.
